Rating: 4
The key to this is to truly carmelize the onions to where they are sweet; extra sugar (about double the recipe) and a tin of anchovies really helps). I did a provalone topping for extra goodness and it was a hit with even the staunchest anchovie haters.

Rating: 3
A big hit with my guests, and pretty simple to make. I'm probably blind, but I couldn't find frozen or fresh pizza dough in my "specialty" grocer's freezer, so I just caved and made my own, which is very straightforward. Like any good pizza, the fresh crust makes a difference, and I'd do it again this way in the future.

